The paper discusses pre-training tasks for language understanding, specifically in the context of reading comprehension and question answering. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques and neural networks, which are commonly associated with sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval and text mining, which could potentially fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
